  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n                        \u003cp\u003eIn Lviv, Ukraine, the \u003ca href=\"https://kmdesignlab.com/en/projects/km-home/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener external noreferrer\" data-wpel-link=\"external\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eKM Home\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e is an apartment that spans just over 1,000 square feet and is the private residence of designer Karina Mayer and architect Danylo Koshulynskyy, co-founders of the acclaimed interior studio \u003ca href=\"https://kmdesignlab.com/en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener external noreferrer\" data-wpel-link=\"external\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eKOSHULYNSKYY \u0026amp; MAYER\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e. Rejecting the conventional developer’s layout, Mayer and Koshulynskyy embarked on a transformative journey to create a home tailored to their lifestyle. The original plan, which included a combined kitchen and living area and three cramped bedrooms, gave way to a more thoughtful configuration. The couple introduced two spacious bedrooms, dual dressing rooms, a practical laundry space, and two elegantly designed bathrooms. This layout not only optimizes space but also enhances daily living with an emphasis on comfort and efficiency.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=567753\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-567753\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-2-810x923.jpg\" alt=\"Modern kitchen with wooden cabinets, marble floor, an oval dining table, and mismatched chairs. A minimalistic design with a countertop featuring a built-in stove and a range hood above.\" width=\"810\" height=\"923\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-2-810x923.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-2-800x912.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-2-768x875.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-2.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFrom the moment one enters the home, art takes center stage. The entrance is graced by “Renaissance,” an evocative piece by Ukrainian artist Andriy Voznytsky, crafted from coal. This striking artwork is highlighted by strategically placed ceiling lights, creating a dynamic interplay of shadows and textures. Another captivating piece, “PORTAL” by Lesya Panchyshyn, adorns the living area, illuminated thoughtfully to accentuate its vibrant details.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=567754\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-567754\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-3-810x540.jpg\" alt=\"Modern kitchen with wooden cabinets, white countertop, and appliances. A cutting board with vegetables and a stovetop are on the island. Brown wall panels with integrated lighting are shown.\" width=\"810\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-3-810x540.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-3-800x533.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-3.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=567755\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-567755\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-4-810x1215.jpg\" alt=\"Modern kitchen with wooden cabinets, a sink, and a floating countertop. A balanced stone supports the countertop, with assorted fruits and vegetables on top. Marble floor visible.\" width=\"810\" height=\"1215\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-4-810x1215.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-4-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-4-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-4-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-4.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe absence of corridors is a deliberate choice, eliminating unnecessary spaces and fostering a natural flow throughout the apartment. “Another common challenge for those aspiring to create a truly modern home is the presence of unnecessary corridors, which often serve little purpose other than to collect decorative clutter and subtract valuable space from the main living areas. That’s why we eliminated all the corridors,” says Mayer.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=567756\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-567756\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-5-810x540.jpg\" alt=\"Modern kitchen and living area with light wood cabinets, marble floor, and large windows. Features a central island, dining chairs, and artwork on the wall.\" width=\"810\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-5-810x540.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-5-800x533.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-5.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe open-plan living room and kitchen serve as the heart of the home, designed to encourage both relaxation and social interaction. The kitchen exudes understated elegance with sleek eucalyptus wood panels, integrated Miele appliances, and a Calacatta marble dining table that effortlessly extends to accommodate more guests. A strategically placed block of marble supports the countertop giving it the illusion of floating while offering an unexpected design detail.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=567757\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-567757\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-6-810x540.jpg\" alt=\"Modern living room with light beige sofas, a round coffee table, and a large abstract painting. Marble floor, large windows with sheer curtains, and a dog resting on one of the sofas.\" width=\"810\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-6-810x540.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-6-800x533.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-6.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=567758\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-567758\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-