veneer adds warmth and texture, seamlessly blending with the minimalist decor. Notably, Mayer’s decision to forgo curtains in the living room allows the natural landscape outside to become a living artwork, framed by uniquely angled windowsills.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=567760\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-567760\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-9-810x1215.jpg\" alt=\"Narrow hallway with marble floor, black textured wall art, and a turquoise vase with dried branches. Bright natural light enters from a room at the end of the hall.\" width=\"810\" height=\"1215\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-9-810x1215.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-9-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-9-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-9-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-9.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=567761\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-567761\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-10-810x540.jpg\" alt=\"A bedroom corner with a wooden sideboard holding framed photos and a vase of red flowers. Beige curtains, a bed, and a door are visible. Light creates shadows on the wall.\" width=\"810\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lviv-Ukraine-Koshulynskyy-Mayer-10-810x540.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/01/KM-Home-Lvi